**Conclusion**

Evasive script writing is a technique used to make scripts difficult to understand and detect. By using code obfuscation, anti-debugging, encryption, dynamic script loading, and script hiding, you can make your scripts difficult to detect and analyze. Additionally, by using variable names, function names, conditional statements, loops, and functions that are difficult to understand, you can make your scripts even more difficult to detect and analyze.
